    "creation_date" : 1367153680,
    "answer_id" : 16263085,
    "question_id" : 3435581,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Just like Neil said:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p><kbd><kbd>Ctrl</kbd>-<kbd>Shift</kbd>-<kbd>F</kbd></kbd> -> Text to find = <code>'\\n'</code> -> Find.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>With only one improvement, if you enter <code>\"\\n+\"</code>, you can search for non-empty lines</p>\n\n<p>If lines with only whitespace can be considered empty too, then you can use the regex <code>\"(\\s*\\n\\s*)+\"</code> to not count them.</p>\n"
  }, {
