    "creation_date" : 1370086298,
    "answer_id" : 16872227,
    "question_id" : 3435581,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Although it is not an IntelliJ option, you could use a simple Bash command (<strong>if</strong> your operating system is Linux/Unix). Go to your source directory and type:</p>\n\n<pre><code>find . -type f -name '*.java' | xargs cat | wc -l\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 330884,
      "reputation" : 8788,
      "user_id" : 655224,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Gf0d2.gif?s=256",
      "display_name" : "algorhythm",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/655224/algorhythm"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1450898398,
    "last_edit_date" : 1450898398,
    "creation_date" : 1411138754,
    "answer_id" : 25936871,
    "question_id" : 3435581,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>To find all including empty lines of code try @Neil's solution:</p>\n\n<p>Open <em>Find in Path</em> (<kbd><kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>Shift</kbd>+<kbd>F</kbd></kbd>)</p>\n\n<p>Search for the following regular expression: <code>\\n'</code></p>\n\n<p>For lines with at least one character use following expression:</p>\n\n<pre><code>(.+)\\n\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>For lines with at least one word character or digit use following expression:</p>\n\n<pre><code>`(.*)([\\w\\d]+)(.*)\\n`\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Notice: But the last line of file is just counted if you have a line break after it.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 127792,
      "reputation" : 4606,
      "user_id" : 325209,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 60,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/daddb65bf815297da17a94305633412f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "AA.",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/325209/aa"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1415194529,
    "creation_date" : 1415194529,
    "answer_id" : 26758552,
    "question_id" : 3435581,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can to use Count Lines of Code (<a href=\"http://cloc.sourceforge.net/\" rel=\"nofollow\">CLOC</a>)</p>\n\n<p>On <code>Settings</code> -> <code>External Tools</code> add a new tool</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Name: Count Lines of Code</li>\n<li>Group: Statistics</li>\n<li>Program: path/to/cloc</li>\n<li>Parameters: $ProjectFileDir$ or $FileParentDir$</li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2386817,
      "reputation" : 15845,
      "user_id" : 2087628,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 42,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/376a703596079b375cd1697267a304b9?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "JaskeyLam",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2087628/jaskeylam"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 14,
    "last_activity_date" : 1468574810,
    "creation_date" : 1468574810,
    "answer_id" : 38392546,
    "question_id" : 3435581,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><a href=\"http://plugins.intellij.net/plugin/?idea&amp;id=4509\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Statistic</a> plugins works fine! </p>\n\n<p>Here is a quick case:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>Shift</kbd>+<kbd>A</kbd> and serach for \"Statistic\" to open the panel.</li>\n<li>You will see panel as the screenshot and then click <code>Refresh</code> for whole project or select your project or file and  <code>Refresh on selection</code> for only selection.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/c43HD.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/c43HD.png\" alt=\"statistic\"></a></p>\n"
  } ],
  "owner" : {
